Flavia Hodges 1990, 2003, 2006.","meanings":["From the abstract noun (via Old French, from Latin <i>gratia</i>), this name occurs occasionally in the 15th century, and by the 1540s was among the most popular girls' names in some parishes. It has always been particularly popular in Scotland and northern England (borne, for example, by  Grace Darling , the lighthouse keeper's daughter whose heroism in  1838 , saving sailors in a storm, caught the popular imagination). In more recent times it was famous as the name of the actress  Grace Kelly  (  1928–82 ), who became  Princess Grace  of Monaco. In Ireland it is used as an Anglicized form of   Gráinne   ."],"variants":[]}],"lifeSummary":"Lady Grace Essex was born in 1336, in Widdington, Essex, England, United Kingdom. She married William Fitche in 1369. They were the parents of at least 3 sons. She died in her hometown, and was buried in Widdington, Essex, England, United Kingdom."},"et":{"1336–":"1336–Surnud","1340–1388":"1340–1388","1365–Male":"1365–Surnud","1368–1390":"1368–1390","1370–1431":"1370–1431","1336–Female":"1336–Surnud","1336":"1336","1369":"1369","1368":"1368","1388":"1388","1431":"1431","1365":"1365","1340":"1340","about 1365":"umbes 1365","1370":"1370","1390":"1390","Fitche Castle, Essex, England":"Essex, Inglismaa, United Kingdom","Fitch Castle, Widdington, Essex, , England":"Widdington, Essex, Inglismaa, United Kingdom","Fitche Castle, Widdington, Essex, England":"Widdington, Essex, Inglismaa, United Kingdom","Fitche Castle, Essex, , England":"Essex, Inglismaa, United Kingdom","Widdington, Essex, England":"Widdington, Essex, Inglismaa, United Kingdom","Fitche Castle, Widdington, Essex, , England":"Widdington, Essex, Inglismaa, United Kingdom"},"fi":{"1336–":"1336–Kuollut","1340–1388":"1340–1388","1365–Male":"1365–Kuollut","1368–1390":"1368–1390","1370–1431":"1370–1431","1336–Female":"1336–Kuollut","1336":"1336","1369":"1369","1368":"1368","1388":"1388","1431":"1431","1365":"1365","1340":"1340","about